        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
This is one of my favorite stories from when I was a wee necro:

I was out killing sirens in OOT.  I was at the spire islands soloing the 3 spawns out there.  For those of you who don’t know it, there are 2 spawns on 1 island and 1 on the other.  This is back before PNP and when the sirens out there were still social.

Well, I finish off the second siren of the split on the 2-spawn island and swim over to the other island.  I kill that siren and head back.  When I get back to the 2-spawn island there is this warrior and a magician sitting next to the where the double spawn pops.  I was 12th I think and they were both blue to me.

I say, “Hey guys, I’m camping these.”
The warrior says, “When we got here this camp was empty.  We’re camping it now.”
I say, “I was chasing a runner.” Ok, this was a lie, but I figured if I said I was at the single spawn, they’d tell me to go back there.  It didn’t matter though.
The warrior says, “We have no way of knowing if that’s true.”
I say, “Dude, that’s not cool.”
The warrior says, “Sorry.”

Angry, but not liking to get into it with people, I return to the single spawn.  I med up and wait.  The siren pops and I send in my pet.  All of a sudden there’s a magician fire pet on it too, then the warrior.  Ok, I think, fine.  I back my pet off and swim back to the 2-spawn.  This time I sit where I can see the two assholes approach.  They come back after they finish off the single spawn.

When they get there I say, “Hey guys, camp was empty.  I’m camping these.”
The warrior says, “I told you we have these.  You need to go to the spawns by BB.”
I say, “How about if I take the solo spawn then, and you guys take these two?”
The warrior say, “Nope, sorry.”
I say, “Dude, that’s totally uncool.”
The warrior says, “Nothing you can do about it.  We’ll out damage you.”
That ticked me off.  I say, “This is really a bad idea on your part.”
No reply.

The first siren pops and the warrior rushes it.  Then the mage sends his pet.  I stand and fear the siren.  It does its awkward pathing dance to the water, then swims off.  They try to go after it, but, as usually happens, they lose it.  They come back and the warrior seems a little upset.

The warrior says, “Fucker.”
I say, “You kiss your mother with that mouth?”
The warrior says, “Fuck off.”

The second siren spawns.  The mage’s pet is still off with the siren apparently.  The two of them look at me.  I sit, meding.  After a few seconds, the warrior attacks this siren.  I stand and fear it.  They chase it to the water, then stop.

The warrior runs right up in my face and says, “I’m going to have you banned, asshole.”
I say, “I doubt it, potty mouth.”  Any time I get into an altercation like this I like to keep it clean.  Looks better should a GM ever look into the whole thing.

At this point I run to the edge of the island, over a little knoll from the assholes.  From being out there I know which way the sirens swim.  A few seconds later the first siren, apparently having worked the mage’s pet, comes running up to me.  My pet jumps it and off we go.  It was at about 2/3’s health.  I tear it down.  I sit and med until the other one comes for me.  This one is at full health.  My pet and I finish it off.  The warrior must have figured out what I was doing, because he and his mage friend came running up at the end of the second fight.

The warrior says, “You KS’d us.”
I say, “How can I KS someone at my spawn?”
The warrior says, “I petitioned you.”
I say, “I petitioned you quite a while ago.”  Another lie.
No reply.
I say, “I hear the BB islands are nice this time of year.”
The mage finally speaks, “FU.”

They left.


 
[/quote]</textarea><br>
        </td>
      </tr>

